<br>
I use pretty much only the CD styles but from what others have seen, the blades styles do more damage. A lot of people love by the Fire Blade/Spectrum Blade anytime combo. The 44 style Prismatic Blade chains off of Spectrum Blade but its pretty tough to get a 3 part chain off in RvR. Only problem with anytime styles are they are usually endurance pigs. <p><b>Raeloran Twinblade</b>, 39 Blademaster, Legendary Grandmaster Armorcrafter, Pellinor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ugraydon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graydon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#000000>(10/13/02 1:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~cgbs/images/graydondaocm.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: L40 Respec &amp; style help wanted</span><hr size=1> I considered that spec, it comes out to:<br>
44 Blades, 44 Celtic Dual, 43 Parry, 10 Shield<br>
I was going for that spec but my respec was coming up and at the time parry was broken in rvr and it looked like it would never be fixed so I ended up with:<br>
50 Blades, 50 Celtic Dual, 28 Parry, 7 Shield<br>
Of course the next week the new patch came out and parry was fixed.  If I could go back in time I think I would have stayed at the previous spec.  Still, I think both are fine.<br>
<br>
With the 44/44/43/10 spec you only loose 1 Blades and 1 Celtic Dual style.  1. Brilliant Blade (Blades) which is second style chain to Revenging Blade (Rear Position) but you can still use Revenging Blade alone or use the Celtic Dual rear position chain Snow Shower/Gale. 2. Super Nova (Celtic Dual) which is the third style chain to Ice Storm (Side Position)/Tempest.  Super Nova has a heavy attack speed reduction on target so it is a loss, but since it is side positional and it is the third style in the chain it isn't a loss you'll loose sleep over.<br>
<br>
You won't loose Solar Flare or Meteor Shower which you get at 34 and 39 respectively.  Re: how often your offhand swings, even at level 50 with 50 CD it's only 62.5%.  If offhand swing is that important you could make up for the difference with the RA Duelist Reflexes though most won't recommend that as a first choice RA.<br>
<br>
As for which styles to use, if you check the damage and effects some of the Blades styles are superior.  For my character: Level 50 with spec of 50 Blades, 50 Celtic Dual, 28 Parry, 7 Shield the styles I regularly use are:<br>
<br>
Anytime - Fire Blade/Spectrum Blade<br>
Evade - Blinding Rain/Blizzard<br>
Parry - Tornado/Meteor Shower/Twin Star<br>
Side - Ice Storm/Tempest/Supernova<br>
Behind - Revenging Blade/Brilliant Blade<br>
Taunt - Taunting Blade<br>
Detaunt - Enervating Blade<br>
<br>
